---
import { ClientRouter } from "astro:transitions";
import "../../styles/global.css";
import ProjectDescription from "../../components/ProjectDescription";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <ClientRouter />
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Jovenes Impulsando la Industria 2025</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-foreground">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="fixed left-6 top-6 flex items-center gap-2 rounded-md border border-neutral-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-geist shadow-sm transition hover:shadow"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="16"
        height="16"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        class="lucide lucide-arrow-left-icon lucide-arrow-left"
        ><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"></path><path d="M19 12H5"></path></svg
      >
      <span>Return home</span>
    </a>
    <main
      class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-4xl flex-col gap-6 px-6 py-24 font-geist"
    >
      <h1
        class="text-3xl font-semibold md:text-5xl"
        transition:name="project-jii"
      >
        Jovenes Impulsando la Industria 2025
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600">Hackathon / May 2025</p>

      <img
        src="/images/image.png"
        alt="Project preview"
        class="w-150 rounded-md"
      />
      <ProjectDescription
        client:load
        version1={[
          "I was part of the winning team in Jovenes Impulsando la Industria's IT Challenge, building an app for activity management, performance tracking, and task assignment in operations.",
          "I served as designer and developer, shaping the UI and the core flow for tracking tasks and performance.",
          "Working alongside a software company for the first time was a milestone in my education and I am very glad I had this opportunity",
        ]}
        version2={[
          "I am absolutely humbled to announce that I recently spearheaded the Frontend Architecture and UI Strategy for a high-stakes, first-place winning initiative within the 'Jovenes Impulsando la Industria' IT Challenge. We successfully deployed a mission-critical Field Operations & Human Capital Intelligence System, specifically engineered to optimize the mission-readiness of elite drone flight crews and operational stakeholders.",
          "Acting as both the Lead Interface Visionary and Frontend Engineer, I architected a robust, resilient 'Zero-Connectivity' framework, ensuring that mission data integrity remains uncompromised even in the most remote, edge-case environments. By designing a proprietary evidence-capture and task-validation protocol, I empowered ground-level operators to execute complex workflows, run performance diagnostics, and synchronize high-fidelity proof-of-work directly to the enterprise cloud.",
          "Collaborating at a strategic level with a veteran software corporation was a transformative milestone, providing rigorous market validation for my ability to deliver enterprise-grade solutions. This project wasn't just about 'task tracking', it was about building the Next-Generation Backbone of Aerial Industrial Logistics and proving that I can deliver high-availability systems that survive the friction of real-world deployment.",
          "#EdgeComputing #IndustrialMobility #DroneLogistics #FrontEndExcellence #ResilientArchitecture #Industry40 #OperationalTransparency"
        ]}
      />
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
